      "rationale": "The primary QoI (NIH) is the clinically mandated hemolysis metric specified in FDA guidance. Secondary QoIs (wall shear stress, scalar transport residence time) directly inform the power-law hemolysis model. The mapping from CFD outputs to clinical endpoint is documented and peer-reviewed.",
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
